newsitem.title: USA: CME September lumber posts limit gains late.
newsitem.headline: CME September lumber posts limit gains late.

text.p: CME September lumber futures rose the $10.00-per-tbf daily limit in late trading, before slipping back slightly, and November was up sharply on talk of higher cash lumber prices, traders said.
Commercial buying was noted in September and commercial and commission house buying was reported in November.
Traders said cash spruce was trading Thursday from $417 to $420 per tbf, versus cash quotes Wednesday of $412.
At 1253 CDT, lumber was up $9.50 to $3.40, with September easing from limit gains to trade up $8.50 at $395.00. November was up $9.50 at $360.00.
